fix(harness): add conditional if filtering to PreToolUse guard hook (closes #122)

Add `if: "Bash(*),Write(*),Edit(*)"` to the PreToolUse guard.sh hook
in .claude/settings.json, matching the three tools with deny rules in
guardrail_policy.json. This skips ~50-60% of process spawns per run
(Read, Glob, Grep calls no longer spawn bash+jq for guard.sh).

PostToolUse circuit-breaker left unfiltered intentionally: filtering
would prevent successful non-Bash/Write/Edit calls from resetting the
consecutive-failure counter, causing false circuit-breaker trips.
PostToolUseFailure, SessionEnd, and StopFailure also left unfiltered
(already scoped to infrequent events).
